dc_description_s: This point data layer represents addresses for Taylor County, Wisconsin at year-end 2016. It is a feature class within the geodatabase 'Taylor_Addresses_YE2016.gdb'. [Buildings represent a collection of points spatially located over the main building for any given address. For the most part, in urban areas, there is not a building point located unless the main building would not be physically visible from the road. The data was developed to only show the main structure for a given address, meaning that there is only one building point per address . In the case of duplexes or multi family structures additional building points and site access points are added. By only having one building point per address and one site access point, a one to one relationship is maintained with the site access point.]
uw_supplemental_s: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements. This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2017. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2016. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2017.[This data set was created as a foundational element for the Taylor County Land Information System. The building feature class provides a digital representation of all address building locations within Taylor County and is to be used in conjunction with developed digital road centerline, site access, and driveway feature classes. The building feature class was intended to be used to enhance addressing information within the County.]
